The paper proposes a new kernel function for Gaussian processes that can capture the sequential structure of data, which is relevant to many applications in speech, robotics, finance, and biology. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. The paper also mentions a consequential autonomous driving application, which suggests that it may be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories as well.
